Internal tables -

are dynamic, in-memory data structures used to hold, process, and manipulate datasets with a fixed structure while a program is running.
They function like arrays, allowing developers to handle large volumes of data temporarily before writing to the database or displaying it in a report

3 types- standard,sorted,hashed(key based).


